main event: A housewife in Greenfield, Wisconsin observed a round, orange-red object with a dome hovering first stationary before descending for approximately 5 to 7 minutes on March 26, 1966.
interesting points: The object was observed with naked eye and measured the size of a meat platter at a distance,The sighting took place at midnight and lasted until 12:07 AM.,The weather was reported as perfectly clear with no unusual conditions present.,The object emitted a glow and had a dome feature.,The report came through Project Blue Book and indicated no physical evidence was found.
sighted object: a round dome-shaped object glowing orange-red
